RISE ASCII SCENE 5
#############################################################################################################
#                                      RISE Ascii Scene File                                                #
#                                                                                                           #
#   File:           pt_alchemists_sanctum.RISEscene                                                         #
#   Description:    Participating-media torture test: "The Alchemist's Sanctum"                             #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   An underground chamber where magical artifacts sit amid layered fog and                  #
#                   refracted light.  The scene exercises every medium-transport path using                  #
#                   a variety of geometric primitives (sphere, ellipsoid, torus, cylinder,                   #
#                   box, CSG) to stress non-spherical medium boundaries.                                    #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   MEDIA TOPOLOGY:                                                                         #
#                     - Global haze: thin golden atmospheric fog (forward-scatter g=0.76)                   #
#                       filling the entire chamber.  Makes light shafts visible.                             #
#                     - Crystal orb (SPHERE): glass sphere (IOR 1.52) with dense amber                     #
#                       interior fog.  Volumetric caustics — light refracts through glass                   #
#                       into the fog, scatters forward, glows.                                              #
#                     - Elixir flask (ELLIPSOID): elongated glass vessel (IOR 1.48) with                   #
#                       emerald-green interior fog.  Tests non-spherical IOR-stack tracking.                 #
#                     - Fog ring (TORUS): ethereal blue-violet ring hovering above the                      #
#                       scene.  Pure volume (casts_shadows FALSE).  Tests toroidal medium                   #
#                       boundaries — shadow rays enter and exit the torus tube, potentially                  #
#                       multiple times for rays crossing both tube walls.                                    #
#                     - Fog pillar (CYLINDER): column of dense crimson fog rising from                      #
#                       the floor.  Pure volume.  Tests cylindrical medium boundaries.                      #
#                     - Pillar core (BOX): dense cyan fog box nested inside the cylinder.                   #
#                       Tests nested media with mixed geometry (box inside cylinder) in the                  #
#                       shadow-walk boundary stack.                                                         #
#                     - Aureole (ELLIPSOID): warm golden wisp partially overlapping the                     #
#                       torus.  Tests non-LIFO stack removal when the shadow walk exits                     #
#                       the aureole before the torus.                                                       #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   LIGHTING:                                                                               #
#                     - Narrow skylight slot overhead creates a defined shaft of warm light                  #
#                       through the global haze.  Volumetric shadows are cast by the fog                    #
#                       volumes (colored shadow patches on the floor).                                      #
#                     - Small bright emitter behind the CSG glass lens drives refracted                     #
#                       caustic beams through the fog.                                                      #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   GEOMETRY VARIETY:                                                                       #
#                     - Sphere: crystal orb, mirror sphere, caustic emitter                                 #
#                     - Ellipsoid: elixir flask, aureole wisp                                               #
#                     - Torus: fog ring                                                                     #
#                     - Cylinder: fog pillar, stone pillars, pedestal                                       #
#                     - Box: pillar core fog, room shell, pedestals                                         #
#                     - CSG intersection: glass lens (two sphere halves)                                    #
#                     - ClippedPlane: floor, walls, skylight emitter                                        #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   EXPECTED VISUAL RESULT:                                                                  #
#                     - Warm light shaft from skylight visible in global haze                                #
#                     - Crystal orb glows amber from internal forward-scattered light                        #
#                     - Torus fog ring casts ring-shaped blue shadow on the floor                            #
#                     - Cylindrical fog pillar casts rectangular/oval crimson shadow                         #
#                     - Within the crimson shadow, a sharper cyan rectangle from nested box                  #
#                     - Elongated green shadow from the ellipsoidal flask                                    #
#                     - Aureole overlap with torus shows combined attenuation                                #
#                     - Caustic beam from lens visible as bright streak in the haze                          #
#                                                                                                           #
#   Author:         Aravind Krishnaswamy                                                                    #
#   Birthdate:      April 1, 2026                                                                           #
#                                                                                                           #
#############################################################################################################

> set accelerator B 10 8

##################################################
# Renderer
##################################################

pathtracing_shaderop
{
	name		pt
	branch		false
}

standard_shader
{
	name		global
	shaderop	pt
}

pixelpel_rasterizer
{
	max_recursion		14
	samples				128
	lum_samples			1
	ior_stack			TRUE
}

file_rasterizeroutput
{
	pattern				rendered/pt_alchemists_sanctum
	type				HDR
	bpp					16
	color_space			ROMMRGB_Linear
}

file_rasterizeroutput
{
	pattern				rendered/pt_alchemists_sanctum
	type				PNG
	bpp					8
	color_space			sRGB
}

##################################################
# Camera
#
# Front-right vantage looking across the chamber.
# Low enough to see floor shadows, high enough to
# see the hovering torus and pillar.
##################################################

pinhole_camera
{
	location			5.0 3.5 8.0
	lookat				-0.5 1.5 2.5
	up					0 1 0
	width				768
	height				512
	fov					60.0
}

##################################################
# Participating Media
#
# Seven distinct media exercising the full transport:
#   1. Global haze     (scene-wide, forward-scatter)
#   2. Orb interior    (per-object, glass sphere)
#   3. Elixir interior (per-object, glass ellipsoid)
#   4. Fog ring        (per-object, pure-volume torus)
#   5. Fog pillar      (per-object, pure-volume cylinder)
#   6. Pillar core     (per-object, nested box in cylinder)
#   7. Aureole         (per-object, overlapping ellipsoid)
##################################################

# 1. Global haze: visible atmospheric fog.
#    Scattering ~0.015 over 12-unit room gives optical depth
#    ~0.18, enough for visible light shafts and atmosphere.
#    Forward-scattering (g=0.76) concentrates scattered light
#    near the beam direction for well-defined shafts.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		global_haze
	absorption	0.002 0.0015 0.004
	scattering	0.015 0.013 0.009
	phase		hg 0.76
}

> set global_medium global_haze

# 2. Crystal orb interior: dense amber smoke (SPHERE).
#    Strong blue absorption gives a warm amber glow.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		orb_fog
	absorption	0.08 0.25 0.90
	scattering	0.25 0.22 0.12
	phase		hg 0.65
}

# 3. Elixir flask interior: emerald-green fog (ELLIPSOID).
#    Absorbs red and blue, transmits green.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		elixir_fog
	absorption	0.60 0.06 0.55
	scattering	0.15 0.20 0.15
	phase		hg 0.4
}

# 4. Fog ring: ethereal blue-violet haze (TORUS).
#    Absorbs red/green, transmits blue.
#    Torus tube radius ~0.3 units, so need higher density
#    for visible effect (optical depth ~0.6 across tube).
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		ring_fog
	absorption	0.50 0.35 0.04
	scattering	0.40 0.30 0.55
	phase		hg 0.3
}

# 5. Fog pillar: dense crimson column (CYLINDER).
#    Absorbs green/blue strongly, transmits red.
#    Cylinder diameter 1.2 units, optical depth ~0.9.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		pillar_fog
	absorption	0.05 0.55 0.70
	scattering	0.20 0.10 0.08
	phase		hg 0.2
}

# 6. Pillar core: dense luminous cyan box (BOX, nested in cylinder).
#    Strong red absorption, very strong scattering.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		core_fog
	absorption	0.50 0.08 0.02
	scattering	0.55 0.50 0.65
	phase		hg 0.0
}

# 7. Aureole: warm golden wisp (ELLIPSOID, overlapping torus).
#    Tests non-LIFO stack removal.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		aureole_fog
	absorption	0.04 0.08 0.25
	scattering	0.10 0.10 0.06
	phase		hg 0.5
}

##################################################
# Painters
##################################################

> run scenes/colors.RISEscript

